1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill Nos. 3068 & 3049, Page 7, Section 43.530,
2 Line 23, by inserting after said section and line the following:
3
4 "527.270. 1. Hereafter every person desiring to change his or her name may present a
5 petition to that effect, verified by affidavit, to the circuit court in the county of the petitioner's
6 residence, which petition shall set forth the petitioner's full name, the new name desired, and a
7 concise statement of the reason for such desired change; and it shall be the duty of the judge of
8 such court to order such change to be made, and spread upon the records of the court, in proper
9 form, if such judge is satisfied that the desired change would be proper and not detrimental to the
10 interests of any other person.
11 2. Notwithstanding subsection 1 of this section, no person required to register under
12 sections 589.400 to 589.425 shall change his or her name for the period of time he or she is
13 required to register on the registry."; and
14
15 Further amend said bill, Page 18, Section 589.401, Line 188, by inserting after said line the
16 following:
17
18 "22. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, no person convicted of an offense that
19 requires him or her to register under sections 589.400 to 589.425 shall change his or her legal
20 name for the period of time he or she is required to register. To the extent the person has a prior
21 legal name that was utilized on or after the date of conviction for any offense requiring
22 registration, such name shall be reported under this section as an alias."; and
23
24 Further amend said bill, Page 27, Section 589.407, Line 7, by inserting after the word "birth," the
25 words "biological sex, as defined in section 191.1720,"; and
26
27 Further amend said bill and section, Page 28, Line 62, by inserting after said line the following:
28
29 "8. Notwithstanding subsection 1 of section 527.270, no person required to register
30 under sections 589.400 to 589.425 shall change his or her name for the period of time he or she
31 is required to be placed on the registry."; and
32
33 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
34 accordingly.
